			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Disclaimer</span> This table is not complete, should you have any logged and verifiable information please post to this thread and I will attempt to incorporate it until we have everything complete.  <span style="font-weight: bold">All non-verified information will be in <span style="font-style: italic">italics</span>.</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Pet Basics - Common to all pets 1-49</span>
<br />
<ul>
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Air Pet</span> - Air Elemental Attack, Air Elemental Invisibility
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Earth Pet</span> - Earth Elemental Attack
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Fire Pet</span> - Fire Elemental Attack, Fire Elemental Aura
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Water Pet</span> - Water Elemental Attack
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Previously the pets had innate resistances,
<br />
Water : Nearly Immune to Posion
<br />
Earth : Nearly Immune Disease
<br />
Air : Nearly Immune Cold
<br />
Fire : Nearly Immune Fire
<br />

<br />
Since a recent patch however, pets supposedly use the greater of thier innate resistances and owners resists.  Verifying this actually works is somewhat of a enigma with the RNG of EQ and the shroud of mystery the developers like to keep us in.</span>
<br />
</ul>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Level 4</span>: Pet Level: <span style="font-style: italic">6</span> Max Hit <span style="font-weight: bold">12</span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">All pets regen 6 HP per tick</span>
<br />
Air HP: <span style="font-weight: bold">75</span>
<br />
Earth HP: <span style="font-weight: bold">95</span>
<br />
Fire HP: <span style="font-weight: bold">50</span>
<br />
Water HP: <span style="font-weight: bold">80</span> 
