				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Went on with the lvl 12 pets, heres the numbers I got:
<br />

<br />
Lvl 12: Max hit 18
<br />
Air hp: 230
<br />
Earth hp: 350
<br />
Fire hp: 180
<br />
Water hp: 280
<br />

<br />
By now I noticed a certain pattern, which was that there seems a ranking of the pet hps like this: Earth 100%, Water 80%, Air 70%, Fire 50%. Using this formula, I went to only test the earth pet thouroughly, and then calculate the other pets hp. I tested this for the fire pet and the predicted value was very accurate. Here are the results for the next circle:
<br />

<br />
Lvl 16: Max hit 20
<br />
Air hp: 370hp &lt;- calculated only
<br />
Earth hp: 525 (tested)
<br />
Fire hp: 260 (tested)
<br />
Water hp: 420 &lt;- calculated only
<br />

<br />
If you look at the 60+ pets, the 100-80-70-50 rule still seems to apply, earth 4800hp, water 3350hp, air 3800hp, fire 2400(?)hp. I will use this rule to test the other circles, just evaluating the earth pets hp as accurate as possible, then testing one other pet of that circle to see if there are significant differences.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
