			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Last two circles pre 50:
<br />

<br />
Lvl 44: Max hit 48
<br />
Air hp: 1225
<br />
Earth hp: 1750
<br />
Fire hp: 875
<br />
Water hp: 1400
<br />

<br />
Lvl 49: Max hit 56
<br />
Air hp: 2205
<br />
Earth hp: 3150
<br />
Fire hp: 1575
<br />
Water hp: 2520
<br />

<br />

<br />
Some things of note:
<br />
- These numbers are somewhat higher than what I expected them to be, looking at the old numbers posted in the table here. This can mean two things...either the older tests were faulty, or my tests were faulty. However I strictly took the "how much damage does the pet take before it dies" approach, and tested the earth pet quite extensively. If my numbers are higher than what was expected it could also mean that pets DO regen while fighting, since that would give them the additional 150 or so hp that they can regen in the average 30 seconds that the fights took.
<br />
- The jump in hps from 44 to 49 pets is HUGE. This clearly shows why lvl 49 is considered the "golden age" for mages.
<br />
- Of the circles pre 49, I never noticed the earth pet reaching the max hit. It always hit for two points less than the other pets. May have been random of course, but it appeared strange anyway.
<br />
- The fire pet seems to be on the loser side for hp. However it MORE than makes up for this with its damage output. In fact, the fire pet can take things down that eat the earth pet of the same circle.
<br />
- Damagewise the pre 50 pets are ordered like this, judging from a soloing standpoint: Fire > Water > Air > Earth
<br />
- Finally, the 100-80-70-50 rule gave very reliable results. As said above, I only tested the earth pet several times to get an exact as possible value for its hps, then calculated the other pets hps based on the rule. A single test with each of the other pets then showed that the actual hp values were always within a +/- 25 hp margin of the predicted ones.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
