			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am not sure about pet regen. I have done a number of tests (and have logs of them) for the pre 50 pets. With the strict "let mob beat on pet until pet dies" approach, then counting how much damage the pet took, I got the numbers I posted above. Then I used another approach to determine pet hp, by looking at the percentage of hp healed by Transons, and calculating the pets hps based on this percentage.
<br />

<br />
For the 49 earth pet, both tests result in the same number of hitpoints (I did NOT test all pets with the second method), and this wouldnt be the case if pets did regen while in combat. Even a low regen would result in notable differences caused by the time the pets lived in the first set of tests. So I can only conclude that pet regen is either non existant in combat for these pets, or too low to be of importance.
<br />

<br />
I agree tho that the effect of regen in combat should be most notable with the PoP pets. I will try to perform the same tests with the 61 and 62 pets and see which results I get (did part of this already...see <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=3330&highlight=" target="_blank" class="postlink">here</a>).<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
