				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I tried out the 61 air pet in Acrylia caverns today, and got very odd results. From earlier tests and reports the ward of xegony is supposed to have about 3800hp. This was also my own result when I used the percentage heal method to find out its hps.
<br />

<br />
However in the "let mob hit pet until pet dies" test these numbers were by far not reached. I ran both tests against the same mob, a grimling deathbringer (zoned out between fights). He is green at 64, but can kill an unbuffed pet very easily.
<br />

<br />
I ran at him and waited until he used his HT (581pts...ouch) on me, then moved back and let the pet take over. In my logs, he isnt shown casting so that should not affect the result.
<br />

<br />
First test:
<br />
3333 damage done to Kentik, time 91 sec
<br />

<br />
Second test:
<br />
2996 damage done to Gasobn, time 110 sec
<br />

<br />
So, something is not right here. If anything the pets should at least have near the supposed 3800hp, more if they regen in combat. Any ideas??
<br />

<br />
EDIT: I did not have DS on in options, maybe the grimling had some form of DS on him that I didnt take note of. Must repeat these tests and make sure to fully dispel him before letting pet take over.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
